Subject: [PATCH 21/47] nlm_xlp_64_be: fix the NAE memory bar for XLP832B0

The problem: XLP832B0 can't boot in little endian mode.

The reason: We need to set IO BAR during NAE configuring. Its'
value should be fixed in the function membar_fixup(). And
this function calls is_nlm_xlp8xx_ax() to judge whether the
current board belongs to XLP8XX A series. But is_nlm_xlp8xx_ax()
also returns true even if the board is XLP832 B0, then we get
an incorrect fixed address.

Signed-off-by: Yanjiang Jin <yanjiang.jin@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/netlogic/common/nlm_hal_nae.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/netlogic/common/nlm_hal_nae.c b/arch/mips/netlogic/common/nlm_hal_nae.c
index a035f0d..8b132fc 100644
--- a/arch/mips/netlogic/common/nlm_hal_nae.c
+++ b/arch/mips/netlogic/common/nlm_hal_nae.c
@@ -3280,7 +3280,7 @@ static uint32_t membar_fixup(uint32_t l)
 	unsigned char b;
 	uint32_t fixup;
 
-	if (!is_nlm_xlp8xx_ax())
+	if (is_nlm_xlp8xx_b0() || !is_nlm_xlp8xx_ax())
 		return l;
 
 	b = (l >> 24) & 0xff;
